Description
Title: Senior Project Manager - ExecutionLocation: United Arab Emirates-Dubai-Dubai Silicon OasisOther Locations: * Support Tender Engineers during negotiation stage with the customers, upon demand. * Launch the order process internally and externally. * Manage the contract in front of the customer. * Manage the drawing approvals & contract modifications, with support of design Engineer, BO and Partner support. * Invoices and delivers. * Optimize the Gross Margin during execution. * Specifies external purchases, including subcontractors (with support of purchasing & quality department). * Coordinate with both customers and intra-company interfaces on continuous basis. * Prepare contract review. * Plan all actions & follow up of quality of execution, contracts deliveries, customer inspections, invoicing and commitments. * Responsible for collecting / managing dues BG''s, LCs in coordination with Sales and Finance * Prepare all documents necessary for the follow up of projects activities (reports, invoicing, planning and management of information etc.) * Assess within the group the tools, methods and competencies and propose all necessary improvements and changes. * Close the job, achieving targeted milestone completion, cost, quality and customer satisfaction. * Provide invoicing forecast. * Responsible for recording proper data and project history / progress. * Provide feed back at the end of the project to all relevant departments on weakness / strength and improvement proposals. * Manage modification for the projects under execution. * Take over the responsibility of other Contract (Senior) Eng or Contract Mgr during his/her absence. * Monthly report, Monthly Project review with Finance and Management. * Team building and Development. * Bachelor’s degree in Electrical Engineering. * Not less than 7 years Experience in Project Management /Contracting / Execution /Tendering of MV / LV Equipment and Packages. * Experience of Turnkey Project Business is plus. * Knowledge in MV/LV equipment, with specific focus on MV products/equipments such as MC Set, Ronex, RM6/Ringmaster, GenieEvo, SM6, F400. Transformer or similar type of equipment. * PMP certification is a plus. * Good knowledge of financial aspects and CCO. * Gulf Experience would be a plus. * Very good knowledge / experience in Commercial risks. * Very good knowledge / experience in planning and logistics aspects. * Fluency in English, Arabic and French would be a plus. * Hands on experience in Microsoft office and MS Projects. * Knowledge of ERP system would be a plus. * Quality Criteria. * Target invoicing associated with achieving the minimum required CCO. * Information reliability. * Response time and quality image in front of customers. * Offer optimization. * Very good interfaces and communications skills (extensive interfaces with partners and Schneider back offices).null
